race.description: Celebrating The Life Of Frank Treen Handicap
race.comment: SKYTALKER (2) has finished close up in his last couple of starts, finishing third at Ascot just over 2 weeks ago. The blinkers are off for the first time, and with a drop in class, he is the one to beat for us. FANTAXTIC (7) won here fresh up, and then joined the Paul Hunter stable, and repeated the dose just over 3 weeks ago. He cops a wide gate, but stays in the same grade, and the hat-trick beckons, despite the weight rise. VOMO ISLAND (1) led all the way to bolt in by over 3 lengths when fresh up from a spell, and then had no luck off a wide gate in a tougher field at Ascot, working hard to get handy, before fading late in the run home. He gets a big swing in his draw and can bounce straight back into the money here. SETAGAYA (12) resumes from a spell with a recent trial win under her belt. She cops a tough gate, but will have William Pike in the saddle, and she can't be taken lightly. Each way. PURO (11) as a good record here, and is worth another chance. Include in all combos.
